<Paragraph  FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">OlapGauge for WPF helps in choosing scenarios dynamically, by which KPI information is highlighted via Value ToolTip and Goal ToolTip.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14" xml:space="preserve"><Bold>Value ToolTip</Bold> allows you to view the value, also known as the pointer. Value referred here is the measurement of actual productive amount reached. </Paragraph> 

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14" xml:space="preserve"><Bold>Goal ToolTip</Bold> allows you to view the goal, also known as the marker. Goal referred here is the productive target amount.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14" xml:space="preserve">The following properties in OlapGauge can be enabled or disabled at runtime.</Paragraph> 

<List Margin="20,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">Gauge Header</Paragraph><Paragraph /></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">Gauge Factor</Paragraph><Paragraph /></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">Gauge Label</Paragraph><Paragraph /></ListItem>
</List>

